# NAVYK Frontend Rules

## Design System (CSS Variables)
- --navyk-blue: #1A56FF (primary accent)
- --navyk-blue-light: #EBF0FF
- --navyk-blue-dark: #0D2EB8
- Semantic: --success (#10B981), --warning (#F59E0B), --error (#EF4444)
- Readiness Score: --score-low (#EF4444), --score-mid (#F59E0B), --score-high (#10B981)

## Component Requirements
- Explicit TypeScript types for all props
- Loading state (skeleton preferred)
- Empty state with actionable message
- Error state
- Responsive (mobile-first)

## Forbidden in Components
- Direct fetch requests (React Query hooks only)
- Business logic (hooks only)
- Inline styles (className + Tailwind only)
- useEffect for derived state

## Page Structure (Next.js App Router)
```
app/(dashboard)/route/
├── page.tsx           # Server Component
├── loading.tsx        # Suspense fallback
├── error.tsx          # Error boundary
└── _components/
    └── FeatureHeader.tsx
```

## UX Patterns
1. Optimistic UI for status changes
2. Progressive disclosure
3. Instant feedback (< 100ms)
4. Empty states with actionable messages
5. Skeleton loading over spinners
